'''Bindi Sue Irwin''' (born 24 July 1998)<ref name="familybio">{{cite web | url = http://www.crocodilehunter.com.au/crocodile_hunter/about_steve_terri/family_biography.html |publisher=CrocodileHunter.com | title= The Irwin Family| accessdate=25 March 2001| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150304014611/http://www.crocodilehunter.com.au/crocodile_hunter/about_steve_terri/family_biography.html | archivedate=4 March 2015| deadurl=no}}</ref> is an Australian actress, television personality, conservationist, model, singer and dancer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.closerweekly.com/posts/bindi-irwin-family-moving-us-98520|title=Are Bindi Irwin and Her Family Moving to the US?|last=Faragalli|first=Samantha|date=22 September 2017|work=[[Closer Weekly]]|access-date=13 October 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013125608/http://www.closerweekly.com/posts/bindi-irwin-family-moving-us-98520|archivedate=13 October 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She is the only daughter of the late conservationist and television personality [[Steve Irwin]] and his conservationist and author wife [[Terri Irwin]], owner of the [[Australia Zoo]]. Bindi's younger brother is [[Robert Irwin (television personality)|Robert Irwin]], a television personality and photographer, and she is the granddaughter of naturalist and herpetologist  [[Bob Irwin]]. Bindi has been involved in acting, singing, dancing, rapping, game show hosting, and has created two instructional fitness DVDs. She is also known for winning [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 21)|season 21]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' (U.S.).

